snippet: Republicans, stung from the outcome of the budget battle, could be more flexible or more determined not to lose again.
abstract: Nearly all accounts view Pres Obama as emerging the winner of the government shutdown, having stared down attempts to undercut his health care program or force other concessions, but it is unclear what he actually won; Obama hopes that Congressional Republicans will re-evaluate their scorched-earth strategy, but many fear they may instead double down to prevent Obama from getting the upper hand in future legislative battles.
lead_paragraph: Republicans, stung from the outcome of the budget battle, could be more flexible or more determined not to lose again.

headline.main: Obama’s Edge Over G.O.P. Is Still Unclear After Victory in Standoff
headline.print_headline: Obama’s Edge Over G.O.P. Is Still Unclear After Victory in Standoff
